        <marginalia hand="English_secretary">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
                    <marginalia_text>Dicit, loca quadrata lun[a]e, no[n] cu[m] ☾ ip[s]a dichotomos fuerit, sed quomodocu[m]q[ue] ip[s]a fuerit, aspectus
                    quadratos in [quo] pu[n]cta cada[n]t, observare monet, vt cu[m] ☾ ibid[em] fuerit figura exacte erigatur.</marginalia_text> 
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>He says that there [are] quadruple places of the moon, not when the moon itself was cut in two, but whenever it was, the guadruple aspects
            in which the points fall, he admonishes to observe, so that the moon would be raised when it exactly was the same figure.</translation> <!--JG: Extremely unsure-->
        </marginalia>
        
